# D.3 — Operator-tier fork commands for the recipes meta-skill
#
# Target: github.com/wisechef-ai/recipes-skill (canonical meta-skill)
# Apply via: cat d3-fork-commands.patch >> SKILL.md   (then re-trim to <200 lines)
# Author: Tori — Phase D Plan v5.4
#
# Adds three commands that talk to the new operator-tier forks API:
#   recipes fork <slug>            — POST /api/forks/create
#   recipes publish-fork <name>    — POST /api/forks/<id>/version
#   recipes install-fork <name>    — GET  /api/forks/<id>/install (signed URL)
#
# Also extends `recipes list` with a "Your forks" section (D.5) and tags
# results with a `[fork]` badge in `recipes search`.
#
# Auth: every command sends `x-api-key: $RECIPES_API_KEY`. Operator/Studio
# subscribers get 200/201; Cook tier gets 402 with `{needs_tier: 'operator'}`.

## ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## Append the following block to SKILL.md (commands section)
## ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### `recipes fork <slug>`
Forks a public skill into your private library.
```
$ recipes fork seo-audit-engine --name "My SEO Audit"
POST $RECIPES_API/api/forks/create
  body: {source_slug, name, readme?}
→ 201 {id, slug, source_slug, ...}
```
Errors:
- 402 `{needs_tier: 'operator'}` → upgrade required
- 404 `source_skill_not_found` → typo or private/internal slug
- 409 `fork_exists` → you already have a fork with that slug

### `recipes publish-fork <name> [--bump=patch|minor|major]`
Tarballs the local fork directory and pushes a new version.
```
$ recipes publish-fork my-seo-audit --bump=minor
POST $RECIPES_API/api/forks/<id>/version (multipart)
  fields: tarball, semver, changelog
→ 201 {id, semver, checksum_sha256, tarball_size_bytes}
```
The CLI computes semver from the previous fork version + `--bump`.

### `recipes install-fork <name> [--into=<dir>]`
Installs the latest version of one of your forks.
```
$ recipes install-fork my-seo-audit
GET $RECIPES_API/api/forks/<id>/install
→ 200 {tarball_url, checksum_sha256, size_bytes, expires_at}
# CLI then GETs tarball_url (HMAC-signed, 5-min TTL) and verifies sha256
# before extracting into ~/.recipes/forks/<slug>/
```

### `recipes list` (D.5 extension)
After the standard catalog, append a "Your forks" section by GET-ing
`/api/forks/list`.  Skip the section silently for non-Operator callers.
```
== Your forks ==
- my-seo-audit  (forked from seo-audit-engine)  v0.3.1
- internal-rag  (forked from cognee-related)    v1.0.0  [team]
```

### `recipes search <query>` (D.5 extension)
Matches against user's forks too. Forks render with a trailing `[fork]`
badge so users can tell catalog skills from their private copies at a
glance.

